nergystorage.org/energy-storage/facts-figures" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: black; text-decoration: none; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Airbnb Cereal App Book; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px"><font color="black" face="Airbnb Cereal App Book" size="18px"><span style="font-weight: 400">some figures stating</span></font></a><span><font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" face="Airbnb Cereal App Book" size="18px">&#160;</font></span><font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" face="Airbnb Cereal App Book" size="18px"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Airbnb Cereal App Book; font-size: 18px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">that relatively modest gains in energy storage capacity could produce total savings in the $25 million&#8211;$50 million range for residential, commercial, and industrial consumers.</span></font>
  </body>
