    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      A carbon tax that compensates for the SCC varies by fuel source. The carbon dioxide production of the fuel source per unit mass or volume is multiplied by the SCC to obtain the tax. Based on the mean peer reviewed value ($43/tC or $12/tCO<font size="11.2px"><sub style="line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px">2</sub></font>, see<span>&#160;</span><i>Social cost of carbon</i>, above), the table below estimates the tax:
    </p>
  </body>
