<node ID="ID_1602230080" CREATED="1553798487234" MODIFIED="1553798487234" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      In 1997,<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">Costa Rica</font></a><span>&#160;</span>imposed a 3.5 percent carbon tax on hydrocarbon fuels.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-163" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-163" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[163]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>A portion of the funds generated by the tax go to &quot;Payment for Environmental Services&quot; (PSA) program which gives incentives to property owners to practice sustainable development and forest conservation.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-164" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-164" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[164]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>Approximately 11% of Costa Rica's national territory is protected by the plan.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-165" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-165" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[165]</a></sup></font>The program now pays out roughly $15 million a year to around 8,000 property owners.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-166" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-166" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[166]</a></sup></font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
