<node ID="ID_1702790049" CREATED="1553798487348" MODIFIED="1553798487348" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montgomery_County,_Maryland"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      In May 2010,<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montgomery_County,_Maryland" title="Montgomery County, Maryland" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">Montgomery County, Maryland</font></a><span>&#160;</span>passed the nation's first county-level carbon tax.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-208" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-208" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[208]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>The legislation required payments of $5 per ton of CO<font size="11.2px"><sub style="line-height: 1; font-size: 11.2px">2</sub></font><span>&#160;</span>emitted from any stationary source emitting more than a million tons of carbon dioxide during a calendar year.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-solveclimate.com_209-0" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-solveclimate.com-209" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[209]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>There is only one source of emissions fitting the criteria laid out by the council, an 850 megawatt coal-fired power plant owned by<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mirant_Corporation" class="mw-redirect" title="Mirant Corporation" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">Mirant Corporation</font></a>. The tax was expected to raise between $10 million and $15 million for the county, which faced a nearly $1 billion budget gap.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-210" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-210" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[210]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>The law provided for half of revenue to go toward creating a low interest loan plan for county residents to invest in residential energy efficiency upgrades.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-solveclimate.com_209-1" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-solveclimate.com-209" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[209]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>The County's energy supplier buys its energy at auction, so Mirant would have to sell its energy at market value, which meant no discernible increase in energy costs would be felt by the county's residents. In June 2010, the Mirant Corporation sued the county to stop the tax.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-211" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-211" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[211]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>In June 2011 the Federal Court of Appeals ruled that the tax was a fee imposed &quot;for regulatory or punitive purposes&quot; rather than a tax, and therefore could be challenged in court.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-212" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-212" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[212]</a></sup></font><span>&#160;</span>The County Council repealed the fee in July 2012.<font size="11.2px" color="rgb(11, 0, 128)"><sup id="cite_ref-213" class="reference" style="line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-size: 11.2px"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_tax#cite_note-213" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null">[213]</a></sup></font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_36130461" CREATED="1553798487348" MODIFIED="1553798487348"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      <b>Washington</b>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_1311291599" CREATED="1553798487351" MODIFIED="1553798487351" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_Initiative_732"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      In 2016, a group of climate activists put<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_Initiative_732" title="Washington Initiative 732" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">an initiative</font></a><span>&#160;</span>for a revenue-neutral carbon tax on the<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_elections,_2016" class="mw-redirect" title="Washington elections, 2016" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">November ballot</font></a><span>&#160;</span>in<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_(state)" title="Washington (state)" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">Washington State</font></a>. If approved by voters, it would have imposed a tax on carbon dioxide emissions and used that revenue to decrease the state's<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sales_tax" title="Sales tax" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">sales tax</font></a>, the business tax, and expand the state's version of the<span>&#160;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earned_income_tax_credit" title="Earned income tax credit" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: null; background-repeat: repeat; background-attachment: scroll; background-position: null"><font color="rgb(11, 0, 128)">earned income tax credit</font></a><span>&#160;</span>for low-income workers.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1680144577" CREATED="1553798498073" MODIFIED="1553798498073" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Carbon_tax&amp;action=edit&amp;section=43"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

